The `GenerateCombinations` function is a recursive function that generates all combinations of length n. It keeps track of the current combination being built using the `current` list. When the length of the current combination equals n, it adds the current combination to the `combinations` list. Otherwise, it iterates through each element in the array, adds it to the current combination, recursively calls itself, and then removes the last element from the current combination before moving on to the next element in the array.

Once all combinations have been generated, the `GetCombinations` function sorts the `combinations` list in lexicographical order by converting each combination to a string and joining its elements. Finally, it returns the sorted combinations.

In the `Main` function, we test the `GetCombinations` function by passing an array containing duplicate elements and n equal to 2. We then print each combination to the console.

