Here's an implementation of the quicksort algorithm in Java that meets all the requirements:

```java
public class Quicksort {
    public static void quicksort(int[] arr) {
        quicksort(arr, 0, arr.length - 1);
    }

    private static void quicksort(int[] arr, int low, int high) {
        if (low < high) {
            int pivotIndex = partition(arr, low, high);
            quicksort(arr, low, pivotIndex - 1);
            quicksort(arr, pivotIndex + 1, high);
        }
    }

    private static int partition(int[] arr, int low, int high) {
        int pivotIndex = getPivotIndex(arr, low, high);
        int pivotValue = arr[pivotIndex];
        swap(arr, pivotIndex, high);

        int i = low;
        for (int j = low; j < high; j++) {
            if (arr[j] <= pivotValue) {
                swap(arr, i, j);
                i++;
            }
        }

        swap(arr, i, high);
        return i;
    }

    private static int getPivotIndex(int[] arr, int low, int high) {
        int mid = (low + high) / 2;

        int a = arr[low];
        int b = arr[mid];
        int c = arr[high];

        if (a <= b && b <= c || c <= b && b <= a) {
            return mid;
        } else if (b <= a && a <= c || c <= a && a <= b) {
            return low;
        } else {
            return high;
        }
    }

    private static void swap(int[] arr, int i, int j) {
        int temp = arr[i];
        arr[i] = arr[j];
        arr[j] = temp;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {5, 2, 7, 1, 8, 3, 9, 4, 6};
        quicksort(arr);
        System.out.println(Arrays.toString(arr));
    }
}
```

This implementation uses a single recursive function `quicksort` to sort the array in place. The `partition` function is used to determine the pivot index based on the median of the first, middle, and last elements of the array. The array is then partitioned into two subarrays, with all elements less than or equal to the pivot value on the left and all elements greater than the pivot value on the right. The `getPivotIndex` function calculates the pivot index based on the three elements. The `swap` function is used to swap two elements in the array. Finally, the `main` function demonstrates how to use the `quicksort` function to sort an array.

