Note that this implementation has a time complexity of O(n^2) because it checks each number from 2 to `num` using the `is_prime()` function, and the `is_prime()` function itself has a time complexity of O(sqrt(n)). However, the implementation is optimized to minimize the number of unnecessary primality tests by using the Miller-Rabin primality test algorithm.

