Inside the loop, we first calculate the carry by performing a bitwise AND operation (`&`) between `a` and `b`. This operation results in a number where each bit is set only if the corresponding bits in `a` and `b` are both set.

Next, we perform the bitwise addition by performing a bitwise XOR operation (`^`) between `a` and `b`. This operation results in a number where each bit is set only if the corresponding bits in `a` and `b` are different.

Finally, we calculate the new value of `b` by shifting the carry one bit to the left (`<< 1`). Shifting the carry to the left by one position effectively moves the carry to the next bit position.

