Here's the Java method that transforms a given input string into a string array with each element of length 4. The input string must contain at least 10 lowercase alphabet letters. The output array is sorted in alphabetical order, and each element is unique.

```java
import java.util.Arrays;

public class StringTransform {

    public static String[] transformString(String input) {
        // Check if the input is valid
        if (input == null || input.length() < 10 || !input.matches("[a-z]+")) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid input string!");
        }

        // Remove any duplicate characters
        input = removeDuplicates(input);

        // Check if the input has at least 10 unique characters
        if (input.length() < 10) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Input string must have at least 10 unique characters!");
        }

        // Convert the input string to a character array
        char[] chars = input.toCharArray();

        // Sort the characters in alphabetical order
        Arrays.sort(chars);

        // Create the output array with each element of length 4
        String[] output = new String[chars.length - 3];

        // Fill the output array with the combinations of 4 characters
        for (int i = 0; i < output.length; i++) {
            output[i] = new String(chars, i, 4);
        }

        return output;
    }

    private static String removeDuplicates(String str) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        boolean[] seen = new boolean[26];

        for (char c : str.toCharArray()) {
            if (!seen[c - 'a']) {
                seen[c - 'a'] = true;
                sb.append(c);
            }
        }

        return sb.toString();
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String input = "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxxyz";
        String[] output = transformString(input);

        // Print the output array
        for (String element : output) {
            System.out.println(element);
        }
    }
}
```

This method removes any duplicate characters from the input string, checks if the resulting string has at least 10 unique characters, sorts the characters in alphabetical order, and finally creates the output array with each element of length 4 by combining consecutive characters from the sorted string. The `removeDuplicates` method is used to remove any duplicate characters efficiently using a boolean array. The main method demonstrates an example usage of the `transformString` method with the input string "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxxyz".

